/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:\n  Line 8:   createFallbackRouter,\n\n  Line 11:   resolveFallback,\n\n  Line 12: } from '../../lib/deep-loop/fallback-router';\n\n  Line 36: describe('fallback-router', () => {\n\n  Line 38:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', null))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 45:     expect(resolveFallback('deepseek-v4-pro', registryWithFallback('deepseek-v4-pro', null))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 54:         const result = resolveFallback(source.id, registryWithFallback(source.id, target.id));\n\n  Line 73:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', 'haiku'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 81:     expect(resolveFallback('kimi-k2.6', registryWithFallback('kimi-k2.6', 'qwen3.6'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 88:     expect(resolveFallback('haiku', registryWithFallback('haiku', 'swe-1.6'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 96:     expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', 'missing-model'))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 103:     expect(resolveFallback('missing-model', registryWithFallback('swe-1.6', null))).toEqual({\n\n  Line 128:     const router = createFallbackRouter(registry);\n\n  Line 163:     expect(() => createFallbackRouter(registry)).toThrow(\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:\n  Line 92: `lib/deep-loop/` holds the loop infrastructure. `executor-config` parses per-iteration executor settings from a shared schema so every consumer calls the same executor shape. `executor-audit` appends a provenance block to each iteration JSONL so you can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration. `prompt-pack` renders the iteration prompt template. `post-dispatch-validate` checks that an iteration produced valid markdown, JSONL and delta outputs before the state log accepts them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` checks permission scope before touching sensitive paths. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/executor-audit.md:\n  Line 62: - [fallback-router.md](fallback-router.md) — Fallback router\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md:\n  Line 5:   - \"fallback-router typed reroute\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"fallback-router-typed-reroute\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"fallback-router typed reroute deep-loop-runtime\"\n\n  Line 8:   - \"executor fallback-router typed reroute\"\n\n  Line 40: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Runtime | typed fallback-router reroute + graph preflight. |\n\n  Line 46: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Test | Primary regression coverage for Fallback-router typed reroute. |\n\n  Line 55: - Feature file path: `01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`\n\n  Line 56: - Source phase: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/030-deep-loop-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/015-fallback-router-typed-reroute`\n\n  Line 57: - Primary sources: `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Us